## Ontology Pitfalls Detector Integration

### Context
Integrated the D2KLab Ontology-Pitfalls-Detector (Apache-2.0) into OntoBricks as a
new "Pitfalls" analysis panel on the ontology page. The library detects 19 structural,
logical, and semantic pitfalls (P1.1–P4.7) across four categories, backed by an async
TaskManager job and a new sidebar section with pattern selector and accordion results UI.

### Changes

1. **`src/back/core/w3c/pitfalls/__init__.py`** — new subpackage: re-exports `PitfallsService`
2. **`src/back/core/w3c/pitfalls/utils.py`** — vendored utility functions (camelCase split, normalize, sort); heavy nltk import moved inside `ensure_nltk_resource` to avoid breaking imports when optional deps are absent
3. **`src/back/core/w3c/pitfalls/runner.py`** — vendored `OntologyPatternToolkit` with all 19 `run_p*` methods; numpy/sentence-transformers/sklearn imported via try/except at module level so taxonomy constants are always accessible
4. **`src/back/core/w3c/pitfalls/PitfallsService.py`** — new service: serializes rdflib Graph to temp TTL, runs toolkit, returns `{metadata, selected_pitfalls, results, grouped_results}`; `get_taxonomy()` and `get_available_patterns()` work without optional deps
5. **`src/back/core/w3c/__init__.py`** — added `PitfallsService` to exports
6. **`src/api/routers/internal/ontology.py`** — added three routes: `GET /ontology/pitfalls/taxonomy`, `POST /ontology/pitfalls/analyze` (async via TaskManager + threading), `GET /ontology/pitfalls/results/{task_id}`
7. **`pyproject.toml`** — added `[project.optional-dependencies] pitfalls` group: sentence-transformers, scikit-learn, nltk, scipy
8. **`src/front/config/menu_config.json`** — added "Pitfalls" item (id: pitfalls, icon: bi-bug) under the "Advanced" ontology group
9. **`src/front/templates/ontology.html`** — added `<div id="pitfalls-section">` + partial include + JS script tag
10. **`src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_pitfalls.html`** — new partial: pattern selector (grouped checkboxes), progress bar, results accordion with per-category cards, empty state
11. **`src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-pitfalls.js`** — new JS module (`PitfallsModule`): lazy init, taxonomy load, run/poll cycle, grouped results render, deps-missing warning
12. **`src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-init.js`** — added `case 'pitfalls'` branch to `_initSectionByName`
13. **`tests/units/ontology/test_pitfalls_service.py`** — new test file: 22 tests covering taxonomy, utils (camelCase, normalize, sort, parse), service grouping, and (skipped when deps absent) run_analysis with synthetic TTL fixtures

